* Iron Raptor just growled*

" I still don't like this..."

IRIS: " And just who said you had to like this? Liking it has nothing to do 
with it, getting through it alive is what matters."

* But then Prowl picked up the monitor and got onto Iron Raptors back, the 
distressed she-bot shaking herself a bit to settle Prowl in the right spot.
She was just as nervouse as he and she could feel it, still having it in her 
mind that he didn't have to do this and it wasn't worth it.

Iris could hear Prowls nervouse sparkbeat.*

IRIS: " Settle down! Being nervouse can only make it worse!"

* But with that Iron Raptoe began to move off towards the direction where 
Iris said to go, to an open plain but far from any bots or ships. Which 
wasn't difficult.*
